<HEADLINE>PHARMACEUTICALS Biotech shares soar</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>21</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975093765</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
SHARES in British Biotech continued to soar yesterday having reached #21
briefly in New York overnight although there was one trade of 10,000 shares at
#26. That followed almost hysterical reaction on Thursday of positive clinical
trials for one of its anti-cancer drugs, Marimastat.
This is an oral drug apparently suitable for ovarian, prostatic, colorectal and
pancreatic cancers. It has been involved in tests for eight types of different
cancers.
However, British Biotech has been anxious to play down the initial discoveries
although it has also seen progress with lung and gastric cancers. It pointed
out that it will take some years to complete all the tests sufficient to get
full approvals but analysts are enthusiastic enough to suggest that it could be
a #700m-a-year product.
The shares came off the top and eventually closed 127p better at 1675p compared
with a year's low of 423p.
</TEXT>
