Blood verdict
KOBLENZ: A German court convicted three company executives and a laboratory
assistant for distributing shoddily tested blood products, causing the death of
at least two people from HIV, the virus that causes Aids. The 1993 scandal
involving UB Plasma sent thousands of Germans hurrying for Aids tests.
MP killed
NEW DELHI: An Indian MP from the ruling Congress party was shot dead by unknown
attackers at his home in the southern state of Andhra Pradesh yesterday.
Magunta Subbarama Reddy died on the way to hospital. A bodyguard was also
killed and a friend wounded in the shooting on the day of a planned visit to
the state by Prime Minister P V Narasimha Rao.
Prozac for kids
STOCKHOLM: Problem children in the Swedish city of Gothenburg will be treated
with Prozac, a widely prescribed anti-depressant drug, after tests showed it
made them less apathetic and more sociable.
Sit-up record
BEIJING: A six-year-old boy in east China's Shandong province set a national
record of 4826 sit-ups in less than three hours, the China Sports Daily
reported.
</TEXT>
