<PAGE>23</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>Book Review</ARTICLETYPE>
<FLAG>weekend extra </FLAG>
<GRAPHIC>Illustration</GRAPHIC>
<RECORDNO>975093779</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
Everybody must get Stoned: Stones Restaurant in Avebury, world famous for its
innovative vegetarian cuisine, shared some of its know-how in Cooking with
Stones a couple of years back. Now there are more than 200 new recipes - from
Cauliflower and Cumin Soup, through Broccoli and Potato Souffle to the Stoned
Flummery, a confection of Drambuie, cream and berries - in Stones Spells for
Magic Feasts, by founder of the restaurant, Hilary Howard, published by Digging
Deeper, price #17.95. As well as being beautifully illustrated, the book has a
nifty wire binding which allows it to lie flat and prevents pages flipping over
at crucial stages of cooking.
</TEXT>
