<HEADLINE>Murdina Cameron</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>20</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>Obituary</ARTICLETYPE>
<RECORDNO>975093814</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
THE former matron of Cameron Hospital in Fife and wife of the former principal
of the Free Church of Scotland College, Murdina MacAuley Cameron, nee Smith,
has died in hospital in Edinburgh. She was 78.
Born in the Hebrides, Murdina moved to Glasgow when she was young and was
brought up in the city. After a long career in nursing she became matron of
Cameron Hospital at Windygates, near Leven, caring for long-term patients.
In 1969 she married W J Cameron, who later became principal of the Free Church
of Scotland College, retiring in 1977. He died in 1990.
A bright and vivacious woman and a prominent member of the Buccleuch and
Greyfriars parish in Edinburgh, Mrs Cameron approached her role as principal's
wife with great enthusiasm. Having retired from nursing shortly after her
marriage, she devoted the rest of her life to church work. She had no immediate
family.
</TEXT>
