Special Travel Correspondent Katie Wood looks at the latest travel bargains
IF the film Braveheart won you over to the beauty of the Stirlingshire
countryside then perhaps the tour of Wallace Country currently offered by
Rainbow Holidays will appeal. The two-night break on half board basis is based
at the Winnock Hotel, Drymen.
Following the video presentation introducing the delights of this region on the
Friday night, you will be taken to the Wallace Monument, Bannockburn Heritage
Centre and Stirling Castle as you follow the steps of this great Scottish
warrior. Available during January and February 96, the break costs #72 per
person based on 10 people or more travelling. Call 01905 450400.
n BRITISH Midland's #65 weekend return fare to London should be enough to tempt
many keen shoppers down to London. Valid until December 17, the fare can be
used either as a day return travelling down and back on a Saturday, or
alternatively it can be extended to include an overnight stay, travelling out
on a Saturday, back on a Sunday. Call 0345 554554.
n THE QE2 is offering the chance to spend the pre-Christmas period on board the
world's most famous liner. Departing Southampton on December 15 you can choose
either a New York shopping spree special, or the New York and Florida Special.
Prices for the eight-night holiday begin at #695. See travel agents for details.
n THE popularity of French gites over the past three decades is well
documented. Now there is a chance to enjoy this type of holiday in rural
Catalonia. Vintage Travel is the first UK operator to promote traditional
Catalan gites in several locations. Weekly rentals range from #245 to #575 for
properties with pools sleeping eight to 10 people. Tel 01954 261431.
n GRAMPIAN is set to introduce the quality kite mark to activity centres
offering holidays in their region. Those meeting the stringent training,
management and service criteria will be marketed through a new company,
Activities Holidays Scotland, which will provide transport, accommodation,
insurance and the activity itself, all in one package.
This is the first project of this kind and is expected to become a role model
for all future developments within this expanding market. More than 50
activities are on offer and the brochure will be available in travel agents by
Christmas. Call 01224 648111 for more info.
n EXPECT to see and hear a lot about Robert Burns in the next few months. To
mark the 200th anniversary of the Bard's death, a major marketing push is on.
The International Burns Festival will have literally hundreds of events
throughout 1996 and is expected to attract an additional #4m to Ayrshire and
Dumfries and Galloway. From concerts and plays to travelling fairs and
exhibitions, every kind of musical taste has been catered for. For more info
call Ken Bruce or Toni Marlow on 01292 619200.
n INSURANCE news - Millennium Direct offers a policy which they say is less
expensive than anything you can buy in a post office, travel agent or through
any tour operator. It allows 21 days skiing both on and off piste throughout
the year and covers you for other travel throughout the year. This annual
travel policy costs #75. Call 0800 365 121.
n CLUB Direct is the other company worth checking out. They're offering two
weeks Mediterranean cover for #10.25 per person and ski travel cover from
#28.50 for 10 days. Annual multi-trip policies start at #35, and Backpacker
trips cost #179 for 12 months. Call 01243 787838.
n AA Hotel of the Year Award in Scotland goes to Cameron House Hotel &amp; Country
Estate, Balloch. For providing first class standards, exceptional hospitality
and an outstanding commitment to service it beat all the competition and is
included in the newly published AA Hotel Guide 1996, which costs #13.99 from
booksellers.
n NOW that Disneyland Paris is finally in the black it's not a bad time to
visit: food prices are no longer being hiked the way they were on opening, and
there are all sorts of new rides and attractions planned for 1996. Cosmos, the
market leader for European coach holidays, has an impressive programme of
breaks to the French theme park.
With 300 free local pick-up points throughout the UK, if your backside can take
the long drive to Paris, it's certainly a cheaper option. Prices start at #139
per adult for a three-day holiday, with up to two children under 12 travelling
free if departing between January 12 and February 8 96. Travel agents have
details.
n JILLY Goolden, TV presenter of the BBC's Food &amp; Drink, will be slurping her
way Down Under on a wine lovers' cruise in March 1996. The Marco Polo cruise
takes in the vineyards of New Zealand and Tasmania, with wine tastings on a
daily basis. Departing March 6, the 13-night cruise costs #2950 per person.
This includes round trip economy class air fares from the UK with free
connections from Scottish airports. Call 0171 409 2500.
