<RECORDNO>975093825</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
FURSTLIE can A say whit a braw airticle thon wis fae John Hodgert (the Herald
Essay, November 25)? It sayed whit A'm shair maist o us deep doon inside kent
weel eneuch awreadie, that the ``democratic deficit'' spoken o bi politeecians
is as naethin at aw compared tae Scotland's cultural ane.
As if tae pruive ma pynt, twa letters appear (November 29) fae folk desperate
tae pit doon oniebodie wha daurs tae challenge the God-gien richt o the Inglish
language tae dominate oor lives.
David Wilson decries the ``effete English'' yit wants a monoglot
Inglish-speaking Scotland. A wee bit o tolerance bi him wadnae gae wrang.
Ian Donnelly's claim that John Hodgert wad hae us aw on the road tae the White
Heather Club cudnae be mair wrang. A can mind thon programme weel eneuch an
like monie ither Scots thocht it gey strange that here wis a show supposedly
aboot Scots culture - yit no a single wird o Scots wis tae be heard.
Naw, if oniething the W H Club shid be brocht back fur the likes o Messrs
Wilson and Donnelly. A wee sanitised Scotland whaur the folk that speak Scots
cud be kept weel ootside.
Thankfully the Scots Education Department tak a mair progressive line that
throu time wul help redd oot the dreadit creenge. Weel duin John Hodgert an
mair pooer tae yer pen!
Richard Heinsar,
Convener, Scots Tung,
58 Whitehill Avenue,
Musselburgh.
</TEXT>
