DYNAMICS
n At first glance it looks pretty strange, a new design for some very old
technology. It's the banana chair, and from where your Frontiersman sits
hunched over a smoking keyboard, it looks like the apotheosis of all comfort.
One could go for a snooze given half a chance.
The banana chair is what's known as a dynamic seat which effortlessly tips the
sitter into a series of relaxing positions, the most recumbent of which is the
almost flat- out posture. The makers say it's designed to fit the human form
and sitting in it feels just like floating. It even comes with a relaxation
cassette and a booklet of loosening exercises. Just looking at the picture
makes one's eyelids droop. Originally developed in 1988, a low-down version has
now been raised and made more compact, using adjustable armstraps to alter the
sitting angle. The BC portable folds into a little carry-unit easy to store and
haul out into the garden during the next long-awaited heatwave.
It's selling at #279 from the appropriately named Banana Chair Company on
01773-533626.
The firm have brought out an even more complex version, the Butterfly Recliner
at #495, which looks, to this stressed-out scribbler, the ultimate in induced
lethargy. It's a rocking-chair recliner, guaranteed to paralyse all industry.
Once he is sprawled in one of these, wild horses would be hard put to get this
writer out again.
