RICH HALL - comedian
n THE best Scottish meal I ever had was ``Monster on Toast'' served in
Inverness. Apparently some fisherman had caught the Loch Ness Monster and the
denizens of the town, knowing the value of tourist income, kept quiet about the
whole affair. On the menu, the monster was obliquely referred to as ``tuna
surprise''.
