<TEXT>
q MASSACHUSSETTS-born tenor saxophonist Flanagan and pianist, vocalist and Mojo
scribe Ingham wear their influences on their sleeves, Flanagan's being fifties
Sonny Rollins and Zoot Sims; Ingham's Mose Allison and Mark Murphy. Together
they create a selection of cool and tidy hard bop and dispassionate, resigned
balladry. Producer Adrian Utley, of Portishead, contributes some fine jazz
guitar on one track and should any of his or any other non-jazz fans fancy
taking a chance, they'll find the other nine tracks easily accessible too.
The Bright Field, Paul Machlis (Culburnie)
q HEAVY hints of Micheal O Suilleabhain here: folk melodies merged with
classical voicings and arrangements; and lots of clear, rippling piano work
courtesy of Machlis, the Californian who recorded the memorable Skyedance with
fiddler Alasdair Fraser in 1986. Fraser again contributes some typically grainy
lines but the overall ambience leans further towards craft-shop-friendly
California dreaminess than true Celtic grit.
</TEXT>
