<RECORDNO>975093863</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
JOE HEENAN - comedian
n Being a bit of a movie buff I would have to go for either The Towering
Inferno or Bullitt as my best film. I am a great Steve McQueen fan. Both of
these movies personify the ultimate coolness of this great actor. From the
tremendous car chase in Bullitt to him hanging off a helicopter in The Towering
Inferno he was the 1970s equivalent of Arnie, Sly and Bruce all rolled into one.
n My worst shop has to be Flip Inc. From the moment I walked in there I knew I
was out of place. All of the staff glanced me up and down and thought to
themselves: ``What is he doing here?'' If I needed assistance I had to go to
them as they were not prepared to move away from the mirrors situated about the
shop. I think the words ``chocolate'' and ``eat themselves'' spring to mind.
MY BEST AND WORST
</TEXT>
