<HEADLINE>Highland league</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>33</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975093874</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
CHRISTMAS is coming early for a handful of Highland League clubs, thanks to a
bargain pre-festive sale by Fort William. Five of their top players are
available on free transfers because the Lochaber club is struggling for cash.
Fort William can't afford the travelling expenses for their quintet of
Inverness and Aberdeen-based players and have released them, setting off a
scramble for their signatures.
In a bid to make an assault on the title, the Fort made generous offers this
season to capture defenders Mike Andrew and Billy Skinner, goalkeeper Billy
Neilson, midfielder Alan MacDonald, and their current top scorer Alan Moir, who
is studying at Aberdeen University.
But their challenge has faltered and they have told the players they will make
their farewell appearance at Deveronvale today.
Elgin and Clach are likely to head the queue for the services of the players,
although lowly Forres are expected to make bids as well.
</TEXT>
