<HEADLINE>Wolves close in on McGhee</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>34</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975093877</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
MARK McGhee, the former Celtic and Aberdeen striker, is doing so well as
manager of Leicester City that he is now being sought after by Wolves.
Leicester chairman Martin George has said that the Molineux club have made an
approach but added that they have been refused permission to speak to McGhee.
Wolves are looking for a replacement for Graham Taylor.
