<HEADLINE>Drugs binge leaves one youth dead, another ill</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>3</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975093890</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
Drugs binge
leaves one
youth dead,
another ill
ONE teenager has died and another is seriously ill after a suspected drugs and
drink session went wrong.
Paul Flynn, 17, was found dead in his home in Dunsinane Drive, Letham, Perth,
yesterday morning. His best friend, Craig Low, 17, was found unconscious nearby.
Craig was rushed to the intensive care unit at Perth Royal Infirmary where last
night he was on the critical list.
His parents kept a bed-side vigil as their son was maintained on a life support
machine. Their son's condition was described as ``touch and go''.
The dead boy's parents, John and Evelyn Flynn, were being comforted by
relatives last night.
The boys had spent Thursday evening together at Paul's house and detectives are
building up a picture of what happened in the hours before Paul's death.
A police spokesman said: ``We are investigating the sudden death of a Perth
teenager found dead at his home this morning.
``Detectives and forensic officers are conducting a full examination of the
relevant locations and inquiries are continuing into the cause of the death.''
The matter is being treated as a drugs-related death but it will take two weeks
for toxicology reports to confirm drug abuse.
It is suspected the boys had been taking Methadone.
Paul is survived by a brother, Steven, eight.
</TEXT>
