<PAGE>4</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975093904</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
Aberdeen councillors have saved taxpayers #250,000 by deciding to stick to the
city's current coat of arms. The shadow council, which takes over the running
of the city in April, yesterday considered two options available for a new city
crest.
</TEXT>
