<DOC>
<DOCNO>GH951202-000150</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH951202-000150</DOCID>
<DATE>951202</DATE>
<HEADLINE>No Headline Present</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>8</PAGE>
<FLAG>news digest</FLAG>
<RECORDNO>975093911</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
Man accused of
kidnapping girls
A MAN appeared in court at Leicester yesterday, charged with kidnapping two
girls, aged nine and 10, who went missing in the city this week for three days.
Mr Andrew Breedon, 32, of Leicester, was remanded in custody until next
Wednesday. The girls were found by police.
Widow loses
THE widow of a driver sent out in a lorry with ``grossly defective'' brakes
which crashed and killed six people, Mrs Brenda Waterworth, of Bradford, failed
in the High Court yesterday to overturn a Crown Prosecution Service decision
not to prosecute the vehicle's owners, Fewston Transport, of Skipton,
Yorkshire, for manslaughter.
Python peril
A BURMESE python stolen from a pet shop in Hackney, east London, is ``extremely
dangerous'', Scotland Yard warned. The 15ft snake is pregnant, ``a condition
which makes her extremely short-tempered and capable of strangling a human
being''.
Mercury fear
THE Highland Green Party is calling for an independent inquiry into claims that
the new Inverness Crematorium may be emitting mercury contamination from
fillings in the teeth of cremated bodies. Inverness District Council's
environmental health convener, Mr James Cattell, said there was no evidence of
mercury escaping.
Jackpot card
STUDENT Graham Glass, 16, of Mile End Place, Inverness, has won a #10,000
jackpot with his first National Lottery scratchcard.
Boy for surgery
SURGEONS will today try to save the left foot of eight-year-old Lee McMillan,
of Nairn. Lee, a keen footballer, was taken to hospital in Inverness after a
wall collapsed on him.
Cash for jobs
CASH help is being offered to employers in Fife to recruit 456 unemployed
people, under the regional council's employment grants scheme, which is
celebrating its tenth anniversary.
Tractor boy dies
THOMAS Pemberton, 13, of Kingston, East Sussex, died in hospital at Brighton
yesterday, 24 hours after being run over by a tractor as he cycled to school.
Drugs man jailed
LAWRENCE Kane, 49, of Hillingdon, west London, was jailed for 18 years
yesterday at Aylesbury Crown Court, Buckinghamshire, for his part in a #1.5m
heroin smuggling scheme.
New police HQ
FIFE Police move into #7m headquarters at Glenrothes on Monday. The switch
follows a campaign by Chief Constable Bill Moodie and regional councillors for
a replacement for cramped and outdated former Coal Board offices at Dysart.
</TEXT>
