<HEADLINE>Emma back in form</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>ANDI ROBERTSON</BYLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>30</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975093912</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
SKIING:
EMMA Carrick-Anderson's disappointment at her performance in the opening World
Cup Slalom this season in Vail two weeks ago - when she failed to make the
second run cut, was eased by two consecutive top-10 placings in international
FIS races in the USA over the past two days.
In Loveland on Wednesday, the Dunblane double Olympian took an excellent second
place in slalom, finishing just 47-hundredths of a second behind USA's Kristina
Coznick () who skied to ninth place in that Vail world cup slalom.
On the first run of the technically demanding course, on artificial snow
Carrick-Anderson was only two-hundredths behind the American.
A minor error on the second run robbed her of a possible victory, according to
her coach Kurt Scherl.
In a FIS giant slalom in Winterpark on Thursday, Carrick-Anderson placed sixth.
Her first run was third quickest but she failed to capitalise, losing her
rhythm on the second run. Results:
FIS Slalom, Loveland, USA - 1, K Coznick (USA) 1-35.19; 2, E Carrick-Anderson
(GB/Dunblane) 1-35.56; 3, C Gedde-Dahl (Norway) 1-37.35; 12, S Robertson
(GB/Aberdeen) 1-40.87; 17, K Morris (GB/York) 1-42.74; 24, K McGibbon
(GB/Glasgow) 1-45.06; 25, T Pirie (GB/Aberdeen) 1-45.13.
FIS Giant Slalom, Winterpark - 1, K Ikeda (Japan) 1-23.86; 2, K Kashinagi
(Japan) 1-24.18; 3, K Clark (USA) 1-25.11. 6, Carrick-Anderson 1-26.21; 10, L
McKenna (GB/Aviemore) 1-26.92; 20, Morris 1-28.79; 34, McGibbon 1-30.85.
q LUC Alphand, of France, won the season's opening Alpine World Cup downhill
race at Vail, Colorado, yesterday with a time of 1min. 37.93sec., according to
provisional results.
Lasse Kjus, of Norway, was second in 1-38.47 and Patrick Ortlieb, of Austria,
finished third in 1-38.61.
</TEXT>
