<DATE>951202</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Gun trial  told of two fiancees</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>8</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975093916</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
ULSTER peace talks politician Lindsay Robb had two Scots fiancees, and three
children by one of them, a court heard yesterday. Mrs Margaret Glen, 33, of
Airdrie, told the High Court in Glasgow earlier this week she was in bed with
Mr Robb when he was alleged to have had a gun in a Falkirk pub.
Yesterday it was revealed that Mr Robb had a Scots-born girlfriend in his home
town of Lurgan, Northern Ireland. The court heard this is Ms Debbie Thorburn,
the mother of his three children.
Mr Robb is on trial with five other men, who all deny conspiring to acquire
weapons for the outlawed Ulster Volunteer Force with intent to endanger lives
in the UK and Republic of Ireland.
The five others are Mr John Johnston, 49, of Laurieston, Falkirk; Mr Francis
Hives, 45, of Liverpool; Mr William McArthur, 41, of Bonnybridge; Mr David
White, 29, of Airdrie; and Mr Alexander Davidson, 23, of Lurgan.
The court has heard Mr Robb took part in peace talks at Stormont.
The trial continues..
</TEXT>
