<HEADLINE>Floyd weds for fourth time</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>3</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975093918</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
TV chef Keith Floyd wed for the fourth time yesterday, after a three-month
romance with food stylist Tess Smith.
The 51-year-old celebrity restaurateur and his 32-year-old bride were married
at a register office in Didcot, Oxfordshire.
``Unfortunately we're not going on honeymoon as we're both going back to work
on Monday morning,'' he said.
He added: ``We are going to the local pub to have a few beers and have a good
time. You're all invited.''
Floyd married third wife Shaunagh Mullet in 1991, but the couple separated soon
after.
</TEXT>
