<FLAG>latest offers</FLAG>
<RECORDNO>975093931</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
BIRMINGHAM Midshires Building Society has launched a range of fixed-rate
investment accounts available over one, two, three, four or five years. Rates
start at 6.5% gross over one year, rising to 7.75% for the four-year period.
The five-year term is a step-up account which starts at 6.25% and increases
each year to 10.25% in year five. Limited access is available to funds in this
account, subject to the loss of 180 days interest. No access is allowed to
money held in the shorter period accounts.
Tessa switch
CHELTENHAM &amp; Gloucester is guaranteeing a higher interest rate on its
second-generation Tessa into which holders of maturing Tessas will be able to
switch their funds. The Tessa Plus will be offered from January 1 and at
current interest rates would yield 7.75%. A maximum of #9000 can be moved from
an existing Tessa into a new account up to six months after maturity.
PEP perks
BARCLAYS Stockbrokers is launching Barclays PEP Deal to enable investors to
purchase self-select and single company PEPs. Subscribers will qualify for free
Air Miles on the basis of 450 for those starting a #6000 PEP, plus a further
225 if they also have a #3000 single company PEP.
Illness cover
SUN Alliance is offering a new critical illness insurance policy intended to
complement employers' existing death-in-service or income protection
arrangements. The policy pays out a tax-free capital sum of up to #15,000. It
is available for groups of 10 employees or more and can be extended to include
their spouses and children.
Free advice
LIVERPOOL Victoria Friendly Society has issued two free guides written by
independent journalists, one entitled ``Money Management for the over 55s'' and
the other ``Coping with debt''. They are available in booklet or audio cassette
form. To receive a copy telephone 0800 550050.
</TEXT>
