<DOCNO>GH951202-000193</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH951202-000193</DOCID>
<DATE>951202</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Supermarket seal protest</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>4</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975093955</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
Animal rights protesters have appealed to Tesco to help save seals from being
culled off Canada next year.
The International Fund for Animal Welfare took out full-page advertisements in
national newspapers calling on chairman Sir Ian MacLaurin to ban Canadian
tinned salmon from his stores. He said yesterday: ``If our customers feel
strongly about it, which some clearly do, then it is up to them whether they
want to take action and stop buying Canadian fish.''
</TEXT>
